# BUG-106 cast validity — documentation only.
#
# The TC fix (TypeChecker.zig + typechecker.zbr) is in place: if a numeric/bool/string
# value is cast to a named class/struct type, the TC now emits:
#   "cannot cast 'int' to class/struct type 'Box'"
#
# However, the `expr to TypeRef` cast syntax is not yet usable:
#   - selfhost parser: `to` only accepts `to!` (force-unwrap); `to TypeRef` gives
#     "expected '!', got 'TypeName'"
#   - bootstrap AstBuilder: panics with "unexpected NT TypeRef" when it encounters
#     `Expr9 kw_to TypeRef` in the grammar-generated parse tree
#
# The TC check is correct and will fire once the cast syntax is properly implemented.
# This file is NOT registered in selfhost_smoke.sh until the syntax is fixed.
#
# QUICKSTART.md §30 also notes: "There is no `expr as T` cast operator in current Zebra."
